</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usamadhibots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Samadhi BotS</A> at: 8/1/01 9:34:51 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usnero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>snero</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/1/01 9:32:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's a level...</span><hr size=1> depends on the level of help you can count on, if people are willing to do most of the work for you, brain bite at 39 is more then doable, especially if you can get a group to clear the way to karnor for you or if it's camped hard and you could walk down.   CoM is a little harder but once again if you have some help it's more then doable, if you want to try it at 39 or low 40s get ready to die though, not all that much room for error. <br>
<br>
I've heard that too about the level 50 restriction but not sure myself. Once again if you're in a guild that does vs and trak well then you could get it easy at 52 or so, with your lure you could also make a contribution.  There is only really 4 steps to the epic, vs staff, tola powder, broken golem and phin, our epic is really a joke now, you just need to get lucky.  The hardest part is the phin staff the rest seem to drop pretty easy.  <br>
<br>
edit: it's never really too early to start your epic, the blue crystal staff really kicks ass just be patient there is a fair bit of luck involved in getting the wiz epic but it really isn't hard you just need to keep at it <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usnero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>snero</A> at: 8/1/01 9:34:11 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utanstaafl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanstaafl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/1/01 9:50:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's a good level...</span><hr size=1> 1.) When ever you can round up the help you need.  No wizard on the face of Norrath can solo this quest.  This quest is more a matter of when you can round up the forces necessary to get the parts in KC and CoM.  If you can do that at lvl 39 then by all means do so.<br>
<br>
2.) Sadly things here are degrading badly fast for people not in medium large (20+ lvl 54+s) and larger guilds.  On my server, Innoruuk, Venril Sathir has been camped 24x7 (ala the way guilds camp Zordak Ragefire for cleric epics) for the last few month.  Unless you are in a guild that can muster the forces to put on a 7x24 camp of VS or are on really good terms with one that can this will be a seriously hard part to obtain.<br>
<br>
